1
00:00:07,293 --> 00:00:09,363
The Devil's Hands Are ldle Playthings

2
00:00:35,173 --> 00:00:36,162
[MUSIC PLAYS]

3
00:00:36,333 --> 00:00:37,812
Huh?

4
00:00:40,453 --> 00:00:42,444
I choose to not understand these signs.

5
00:00:45,293 --> 00:00:46,612
Aha!

6
00:00:46,773 --> 00:00:49,287
Bender! I was just
not playing the holophonor.

7
00:00:49,493 --> 00:00:51,563
Yeah, well, you should try
not stinking at it.

8
00:00:51,773 --> 00:00:54,333
Well, I am trying.
I've been taking lessons.

9
00:00:54,533 --> 00:00:56,285
Lessons! Oh, that's rich!

10
00:00:56,453 --> 00:01:00,002
Isn't it time you gave up all hope
of ever improving yourself in any way?

11
00:01:00,213 --> 00:01:02,090
I know I should, but I just can't.

12
00:01:02,253 --> 00:01:04,721
Remember those stomach worms
I had that made me smart?

13
00:01:04,893 --> 00:01:07,566
I could play the holophonor.
And it made Leela like me.

14
00:01:09,653 --> 00:01:12,963
Hey, Bender, as long as you know,
I have a holophonor recital Tuesday. . .

15
00:01:13,133 --> 00:01:15,727
. . .and I'd really like to have
somebody there. Please?

16
00:01:16,293 --> 00:01:17,931
Fine. I'll go already.

17
00:01:18,093 --> 00:01:21,244
You know, sometimes I wish
your real parents were still alive.

18
00:01:22,053 --> 00:01:24,123
Not often, though.

19
00:01:28,053 --> 00:01:29,042
Hey!

20
00:01:29,293 --> 00:01:31,807
[MUMBLING]

21
00:01:32,493 --> 00:01:34,961
-Hello, Mrs. Mellonger.
-Hello, Philip.

22
00:01:35,173 --> 00:01:39,052
And you must be Mr. Bender.
Philip's told me so much about you.

23
00:01:39,213 --> 00:01:43,286
-Is it true that you're a robot?
-I prefer the term "Iove machine. "

24
00:01:43,453 --> 00:01:44,442
[PURRS]

25
00:01:44,813 --> 00:01:46,849
[PLAYS BEETHOVEN'S "FUR ELISE"]

26
00:02:04,653 --> 00:02:06,450
Your kid is great.

27
00:02:06,613 --> 00:02:10,367
-How hard you say you had to hit him?
-Fairly hard.

28
00:02:15,653 --> 00:02:17,325
"The Grumpy Snail. "

29
00:02:17,493 --> 00:02:19,723
[PLAYS BADLY]

30
00:02:24,733 --> 00:02:26,212
Sorry.

31
00:02:29,973 --> 00:02:31,201
[GROWLING]

32
00:02:31,373 --> 00:02:33,887
[SCREAMING]

33
00:02:35,253 --> 00:02:37,244
It's too grumpy!

34
00:02:41,373 --> 00:02:44,604
-No! No! Quit! Stop!
-Whoo!

35
00:02:44,813 --> 00:02:47,885
Mr. Bender, I simply
cannot teach your child.

36
00:02:48,093 --> 00:02:50,766
Then good day, madam!

37
00:02:54,093 --> 00:02:57,051
We hope to see you soon for tea.

38
00:02:58,333 --> 00:02:59,402
FRY:
It's hopeless.

39
00:02:59,613 --> 00:03:03,367
I can hear this great music in my head,
but my stupid hands can't keep up.

40
00:03:03,573 --> 00:03:07,407
You know what always cheers me up?
Laughing at other people's misfortunes!

41
00:03:07,573 --> 00:03:08,562
[LAUGHING]

42
00:03:09,253 --> 00:03:12,006
Hey, guys. You missed a great
delivery to space Earth.

43
00:03:12,173 --> 00:03:14,812
-Where you been all afternoon?
-At a concert.

44
00:03:15,013 --> 00:03:18,847
Was it jazz noodling?
My ex-boyfriend Shawn played the sax.

45
00:03:19,013 --> 00:03:22,767
I used to listen for hours while he sat
naked on my couch and improvised.

46
00:03:22,933 --> 00:03:25,606
So musicians really
Rodger your Hammerstein?

47
00:03:25,773 --> 00:03:29,607
Yeah. It's weird.
Shawn was uneducated, unambitious.

48
00:03:29,773 --> 00:03:32,207
-He was pasty and hunched.
-Pretty boy.

49
00:03:32,413 --> 00:03:37,692
But when he played, I could sense
this incredible, beautiful creative soul.

50
00:03:37,853 --> 00:03:41,528
Then one day I found someone else's
couch fibers on his butt.

51
00:03:41,693 --> 00:03:43,843
I couldn't even believe that.
That's really. . . .

52
00:03:44,013 --> 00:03:46,846
That could be my beautiful soul
sitting naked on her couch.

53
00:03:47,013 --> 00:03:49,322
If I could just learn
to play this stupid thing.

54
00:03:49,493 --> 00:03:50,926
Oh, but you can.

55
00:03:51,133 --> 00:03:53,852
You may have to metaphorically
make a deal with the devil.

56
00:03:54,053 --> 00:03:55,850
And by devil, I mean Robot Devil.

57
00:03:56,013 --> 00:03:58,811
And by metaphorically,
I mean get your coat.

58
00:03:59,013 --> 00:04:00,810
[SCREAMING]

59
00:04:02,653 --> 00:04:04,609
[MUSIC PLAYS]

60
00:04:05,613 --> 00:04:09,686
You hit a sour note about
200 years back, Doug!

61
00:04:09,893 --> 00:04:11,406
Let's take it from the top.

62
00:04:12,773 --> 00:04:15,241
-Ow!
-Bender! Fry!

63
00:04:15,413 --> 00:04:17,881
You've come back
for more eternal damnation!

64
00:04:18,093 --> 00:04:21,688
No, this isn't a religious visit.
Fry just wants holophonor lessons.

65
00:04:21,853 --> 00:04:24,048
Yep. I need to get really good
without practicing.

66
00:04:24,253 --> 00:04:25,971
[CHUCKLING]

67
00:04:26,133 --> 00:04:29,762
Hell is full of 1 0-year-olds
who wanted exactly the same thing.

68
00:04:29,933 --> 00:04:32,606
Trouble is, you have what
my old music teacher. . .

69
00:04:32,773 --> 00:04:36,482
. . .Mrs. Mellonger, calls "stupid fingers. "

70
00:04:36,653 --> 00:04:40,009
With hands like that
you'll be lucky to master a belt buckle.

71
00:04:41,733 --> 00:04:46,090
Now, wouldn't it be nice if you had
a pair of robot hands to replace them?

72
00:04:46,373 --> 00:04:49,171
Sure would. Oh, well, goodbye.

73
00:04:49,333 --> 00:04:50,686
Fry, you smelly idiot.

74
00:04:50,853 --> 00:04:54,084
I think he's willing to make some kind
of deal with the devil with you.

75
00:04:54,253 --> 00:04:56,084
He is? Great!

76
00:04:56,253 --> 00:04:58,687
-Wait, what's the catch?
-No catch.

77
00:04:58,853 --> 00:05:02,129
I'll merely pick a robot at random
from somewhere in the universe. . .

78
00:05:02,293 --> 00:05:05,603
. . .probably one you've never even met,
and then I'll remove his hands. . .

79
00:05:05,773 --> 00:05:09,243
. . .and switch them for yours.
It's just the sort of guy I am.

80
00:05:09,413 --> 00:05:11,927
-What do you say?
-I don't know.

81
00:05:12,093 --> 00:05:15,529
-It doesn't seem entirely moral to--
-Fry, if you don't take this offer. . .

82
00:05:15,693 --> 00:05:18,002
. . .I will lose all respect
for you and punch you.

83
00:05:18,213 --> 00:05:19,612
[CHUCKLING]

84
00:05:19,853 --> 00:05:22,003
Well, all right.

85
00:05:22,173 --> 00:05:24,926
-You sure I won't know him?
-Definitely probably not.

86
00:05:25,093 --> 00:05:27,288
-Just sign this contract.
-Wow.

87
00:05:29,453 --> 00:05:31,364
And here we go!

88
00:05:34,053 --> 00:05:37,363
I got 1 00 bucks on Rectal Exam-bot!

89
00:05:51,653 --> 00:05:55,726
-Ah!
-Robot Devil? I get your hands?

90
00:05:55,893 --> 00:05:58,805
Oh, what an appallingly ironic outcome!

91
00:05:58,973 --> 00:06:04,650
It's not ironic, it's just coincidental.
Now fork over those ladyfingers, cookie!

92
00:06:06,413 --> 00:06:10,292
I only put my name on there as a show
of good faith for the other robots.

93
00:06:10,493 --> 00:06:13,053
Stop being such a baby
and chop my hands off.

94
00:06:13,253 --> 00:06:15,847
Oh, very well.

95
00:06:17,093 --> 00:06:20,881
-How'd you do that?
-They're very good hands.

96
00:06:21,093 --> 00:06:24,768
At last! At last I have the power
to make Leela love me!

97
00:06:24,933 --> 00:06:26,889
[GAGGING]

98
00:06:27,253 --> 00:06:30,643
Oh, sorry. That'll wear off
in a couple of days.

99
00:06:35,973 --> 00:06:38,009
Check it out, everyone!
I'm back from hell. . .

100
00:06:38,173 --> 00:06:40,846
-. . .and I've got the Robot Devil's hands!
-Neat!

101
00:06:41,013 --> 00:06:43,891
-Let's see a trick!
-Alrighty.

102
00:06:44,053 --> 00:06:45,406
[BENDER BABBLING]

103
00:06:47,933 --> 00:06:51,642
Somebody called a Robot Devil's here
to see somebody called Fry.

104
00:06:51,893 --> 00:06:53,121
Uh-oh.

105
00:06:54,613 --> 00:06:56,331
Where'd I go just now?

106
00:06:57,693 --> 00:06:59,445
Hello, Fry.

107
00:06:59,613 --> 00:07:01,251
[CHUCKLING]

108
00:07:01,413 --> 00:07:05,167
Just dropped by to make sure you're as
happy with our little deal as I am.

109
00:07:05,333 --> 00:07:08,803
And-- Oh, give me back my hands!

110
00:07:08,973 --> 00:07:12,648
These things are always
touching me in places.

111
00:07:12,853 --> 00:07:13,842
[CHUCKLING]

112
00:07:14,013 --> 00:07:17,210
Yeah, they get around.
But I'm afraid we had a deal.

113
00:07:17,453 --> 00:07:21,571
-Looks like I wasted a bus trip.
-Yes, you did.

114
00:07:21,813 --> 00:07:24,247
[HOLOPHONOR PLAYS]

115
00:07:31,293 --> 00:07:33,443
[PLAYS "FUR ELISE"]

116
00:07:38,653 --> 00:07:40,086
[WOMAN SCREAMS]

117
00:07:42,373 --> 00:07:45,012
[CARMEN'S "BOLERO" PLAYS]

118
00:07:54,533 --> 00:07:57,684
Yes, now you can hear
holophonor virtuoso Philip Fry...

119
00:07:57,853 --> 00:08:02,085
...playing 900 of these classic themes in
your own home on this two-record set.

120
00:08:02,253 --> 00:08:05,404
That's over 30 minutes
of music for only $ 14.99.

121
00:08:05,733 --> 00:08:10,648
Only $1 4.99 for a two-record set.
Two records!

122
00:08:10,853 --> 00:08:14,846
Oh, Zoidberg, at last you're becoming
a crafty consumer.

123
00:08:15,013 --> 00:08:17,322
MAN: Hello?
-Hello? I'll take eight!

124
00:08:17,493 --> 00:08:18,528
[DOORBELL CHIMES]

125
00:08:19,453 --> 00:08:22,570
-A Mr. Hedonism-bot to see you.
-Show him in.

126
00:08:22,773 --> 00:08:26,971
-Very good, sir.
-Oh, Fry! Congratulations!

127
00:08:27,133 --> 00:08:30,330
Your latest performance was
as delectable as dipping my bottom. . .

128
00:08:30,493 --> 00:08:34,406
. . .over and over into a bath
of the silkiest oils and creams.

129
00:08:34,613 --> 00:08:36,922
Thank you. That's exactly
what I was going for.

130
00:08:37,133 --> 00:08:41,604
You are the sole diversion in what has
been a pale and unamusing season.

131
00:08:41,773 --> 00:08:45,686
And so I would fain commission
you write an opera.

132
00:08:45,893 --> 00:08:49,727
-But I've never written an opera.
-And I've never heard one.

133
00:08:49,893 --> 00:08:52,612
Still, if you can keep me amused
through the overture. . .

134
00:08:52,773 --> 00:08:55,367
. . .I shall consider it a smashing success.

135
00:08:55,573 --> 00:08:58,645
But I wouldn't even know
what to write about. Unless. . . .

136
00:09:03,653 --> 00:09:07,009
Okay, I'll do it.
If I can make it about Leela.

137
00:09:07,213 --> 00:09:08,726
Me? Really?

138
00:09:08,973 --> 00:09:12,727
A man writing an opera about a woman?

139
00:09:13,173 --> 00:09:18,372
Oh, sirrah. How deliciously absurd.
I shall see you at the premiere.

140
00:09:18,533 --> 00:09:20,524
[GIGGLING]

141
00:09:24,973 --> 00:09:28,045
[HOLOPHONOR PLAYS]

142
00:09:41,893 --> 00:09:44,726
-Is it part of the opera?
-Leela! You shouldn't be listening.

143
00:09:44,933 --> 00:09:48,323
-I don't want you to hear it till it's done.
-But it's so beautiful.

144
00:09:48,533 --> 00:09:51,093
So is a peacock, but you don't
eat it until it's cooked.

145
00:09:51,253 --> 00:09:52,527
This has to be perfect.

146
00:09:52,693 --> 00:09:56,049
I want you to hear exactly
what I hear when I think about you.

147
00:09:56,253 --> 00:10:00,804
Oh, Fry. All this time you've had
this incredible gift and I never knew.

148
00:10:00,973 --> 00:10:04,568
I've been a fool.
A fully justified, prudent fool.

149
00:10:06,933 --> 00:10:10,972
-Ah! They're so cold!
ROBOT DEVIL: And yet hell is so hot!

150
00:10:11,133 --> 00:10:13,169
[ROBOT DEVIL LAUGHING]

151
00:10:13,333 --> 00:10:15,642
ROBOT DEVIL: Can I have my hands?
-No!

152
00:10:15,813 --> 00:10:17,531
You're not nice!

153
00:10:19,653 --> 00:10:21,689
[HUMMING]

154
00:10:23,693 --> 00:10:29,131
Bender, this is a surprise.
For you, finding me in the refrigerator!

155
00:10:29,333 --> 00:10:32,131
True, but at least I don't have
the hiccups anymore. What up?

156
00:10:32,293 --> 00:10:35,683
Oh, well, it so happens I'm in the mood
to make a deal with you.

157
00:10:35,853 --> 00:10:40,847
-Forget it, you can't tempt me.
-Really? There's nothing you want?

158
00:10:41,013 --> 00:10:44,050
I forgot you could tempt me
with things I want.

159
00:10:44,253 --> 00:10:48,610
I suppose I've always wondered what
it would be like to be more annoying.

160
00:10:48,773 --> 00:10:51,333
Oh. Nothing simpler.

161
00:10:51,493 --> 00:10:56,806
And all I ask in return is your hands
to replace these bony hot dogs.

162
00:10:57,013 --> 00:11:00,005
Grabby and Squeezy? Never!
I love these guys!

163
00:11:00,213 --> 00:11:02,886
Is there anything else
you would part with?

164
00:11:03,093 --> 00:11:06,324
No! Nothing! Ain't gonna happen.

165
00:11:07,373 --> 00:11:11,286
Yes! With this built-in stadium air horn,
I can really annoy people!

166
00:11:11,453 --> 00:11:13,967
And all it cost me was my crotch plate.

167
00:11:14,133 --> 00:11:18,012
You certainly are a shrewd
businessman, Bender.

168
00:11:18,173 --> 00:11:20,607
Now find someone
and give them a good blast.

169
00:11:20,893 --> 00:11:24,602
Yeah! That'll teach
the first person I see a lesson.

170
00:11:24,813 --> 00:11:29,045
My ridiculously circuitous plan
is one quarter complete.

171
00:11:29,213 --> 00:11:31,204
[LAUGHING]

172
00:11:32,733 --> 00:11:34,849
Well, Fry's opera premieres
tomorrow night.

173
00:11:35,013 --> 00:11:38,642
I'm off to find a pair of formal gloves
that'll fit over my enormous forearms.

174
00:11:39,693 --> 00:11:42,002
[AIR HORN HONKING]

175
00:11:43,333 --> 00:11:44,322
[LAUGHING]

176
00:11:44,493 --> 00:11:47,644
-Pretty annoying, huh, Leela?
-What? Are you talking?

177
00:11:47,813 --> 00:11:50,532
-Oh, God, I'm deaf!
-Oops!

178
00:11:50,693 --> 00:11:54,003
I'm so, so sorry, Leela.
I just wanted to annoy you.

179
00:11:54,213 --> 00:11:58,968
What? Oh, this is horrible!
I won't be able to hear Fry's opera.

180
00:11:59,133 --> 00:12:01,124
[SOBBING]

181
00:12:01,293 --> 00:12:03,602
Oh, how delightfully ironic.

182
00:12:03,813 --> 00:12:07,362
It's not ironic. It's just mean.
Take this:

183
00:12:07,533 --> 00:12:08,852
[AIR HORN FADING]

184
00:12:09,093 --> 00:12:12,847
Oh! Out of aerosol. Also ironic.

185
00:12:13,053 --> 00:12:15,931
Oh, yeah? Well, bite my shiny metal--

186
00:12:16,093 --> 00:12:19,005
Oh, no!

187
00:12:28,133 --> 00:12:29,691
Nobody tell Fry I'm deaf.

188
00:12:29,853 --> 00:12:32,970
If he found out I couldn't hear his opera,
it'd break his heart.

189
00:12:33,173 --> 00:12:34,322
Okay, Deafo.

190
00:12:35,813 --> 00:12:41,092
Courtesans and gentle fops,
I bid you welcome to my opera.

191
00:12:41,253 --> 00:12:46,486
Let us cavort like the Greeks of old.
You know the ones I mean.

192
00:12:50,693 --> 00:12:52,411
[CROWD MUMBLING]

193
00:12:52,813 --> 00:12:54,644
-Hurrah!
-Yay, Fry!

194
00:12:54,853 --> 00:12:56,605
I watch TV with that guy!

195
00:13:11,253 --> 00:13:14,165
Who is this one-eyed
Female baby Moses?

196
00:13:14,333 --> 00:13:17,962
With courage in
Her female baby smile?

197
00:13:18,133 --> 00:13:20,966
A savior from the stars
Or something stranger still?

198
00:13:21,173 --> 00:13:26,008
Orjust a lonely
Filthy, starving child?

199
00:13:26,213 --> 00:13:29,808
Amy, Fry's looking at me.
What am I supposed to be feeling?

200
00:13:31,693 --> 00:13:33,172
Ah.

201
00:13:35,853 --> 00:13:40,290
Leela, Leela, Leela, save him

202
00:13:40,493 --> 00:13:45,408
Save Fry, save Fry
Godzilla will devour him

203
00:13:45,573 --> 00:13:49,532
As for me, I must be off
To have my doctor check this cough

204
00:13:49,693 --> 00:13:50,682
[COUGHING]

205
00:13:50,853 --> 00:13:52,684
Goodbye

206
00:13:53,773 --> 00:13:58,244
I don't recall ever fighting Godzilla.
But that is so what I would've done.

207
00:14:01,173 --> 00:14:02,731
[LAUGHING]

208
00:14:03,173 --> 00:14:05,084
One diet double martini, please.

209
00:14:05,253 --> 00:14:08,165
-And for you, sir?
-I'll just have a Shirley Hemple.

210
00:14:08,333 --> 00:14:12,884
Extra! Extra!
World's greatest opera only half over!

211
00:14:13,053 --> 00:14:14,327
Half over? Oh!

212
00:14:15,093 --> 00:14:18,972
-I'd give anything to hear the rest.
-Anything?

213
00:14:20,293 --> 00:14:24,047
Thank you, sir.
Now, as I was saying, anything?

214
00:14:24,213 --> 00:14:27,205
Because I can give you new robotic ears.

215
00:14:27,413 --> 00:14:29,449
What?
You can give me new ears?

216
00:14:29,613 --> 00:14:33,208
Wait. What seemingly reasonable
thing do you want in return?

217
00:14:33,413 --> 00:14:37,247
-Just your hands, my dear.
-Whatever you said, forget it.

218
00:14:37,453 --> 00:14:39,489
All right, then. Just one hand.

219
00:14:39,813 --> 00:14:42,611
Just my left hand?

220
00:14:43,893 --> 00:14:48,523
MAN: Please take your seats for Act 2.
HEDONISM-BOT: I'm not done vomiting!

221
00:14:50,933 --> 00:14:52,844
I can't stand it!

222
00:14:53,053 --> 00:14:58,286
-Okay! You can have my hand.
-Wonderful! Just sign here.

223
00:14:58,773 --> 00:15:01,685
Calculon, old friend,
I'm afraid I need your ears.

224
00:15:01,893 --> 00:15:08,207
Well, I do owe you for giving me
this unholy acting talent!

225
00:15:11,173 --> 00:15:13,846
[ORCHESTRA TUNING]

226
00:15:14,013 --> 00:15:17,164
I can hear!
I can hear like a safecracker!

227
00:15:17,373 --> 00:15:22,891
-Hey, aren't you gonna take my hand?
-In good time. You go enjoy the opera.

228
00:15:27,973 --> 00:15:31,124
To win Leela 's heart
With the holophonor's art

229
00:15:31,333 --> 00:15:34,166
I need hands
Of transcendental quickness

230
00:15:34,373 --> 00:15:39,083
Well, I don 't see any danger
ln gambling with a stranger

231
00:15:39,373 --> 00:15:44,367
For my head is
Of a most amazing thickness

232
